[normal]Written evidence from the Association of Personal Injury Lawyers (CMI0014)[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The 
[normal] Association of Personal Injury Lawyers (APIL) is a not-for-profit organisation with 
[normal]more than
[normal] 20
[normal] 
[normal]year
[normal]s’
[normal] history of working to help injured people gain the access to justice they need and deserve.  
[normal]We have more than 
[normal]4,
[normal]0
[normal]00 members 
[normal]who 
[normal]are committed to suppo
[normal]rting the association’s aims, and all are signed up to APIL’s code of conduct and consumer charter.  Membership comprises mostly solicitors, along with barristers, legal executives, paralegals and some academics.
[normal]  [bold]&#xa0;[bold]Medical evidence[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]road traffic claims where the only injuries are soft tissue ‘whiplash’ injuries to the back, shoulders and neck;
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]road traffic claims involving 
[normal]all 
[normal]soft tissue injuries, whether caused by whiplash or otherwise (for example knee strain);
[normal]c)
[normal]              
[normal]road tr
[normal]affic claims where there are mixed injuries including whiplash injuiries, such as whiplash plus a broken leg;
[normal]d)
[normal]              
[normal]all road traffic claims up to a specified value which are covered by the current protocol, whether or not whiplash is included (such as psychol
[normal]ogical damage).
